{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"96ece62e-beca-4c3f-a482-8875f9527854","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` was **rewritten to use Microsoft Testing Platform natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 bridge to opt into MTP; it's **no longer needed** on .NET 10.\n\nYou can simply remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QeTgEV76kPV4yFMdiyhYLt","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013gtvvRXxout3MSNEeWQ3EQ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5fe8dd11999944fd8caa49bc881e0cb6/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":""},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5fe8dd11999944fd8caa49bc881e0cb6/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"01f7048e-3104-437a-96a8-2a7eaa793561","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me provide accurate guidance.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. The .NET 10 SDK's `dotnet test` command was rewritten to use MTP natively.\n\nKey points:\n- In .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default for projects that have `EnableMSTestRunner=true` (or similar runner enablement)\n- `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed — it was a bridge property for .NET 9 to opt into the MTP-based `dotnet test` experience\n\n\n- Since they're on .NET 10, they can safely remove that property from their project file.","outputTokens":484,"requestId":"7039:738C1:DE86695:F4C1FB2:69F2A8E6"},"id":"8b3393e4-c25e-4ca6-a5c5-241aee5fce01","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:57:19.380Z","parentId":"f119838b-6e60-4c40-baa3-27e078322382"}
